{"action": "input", "code": "def get_most_common_color_in_block(input_grid: np.ndarray, i: int, j: int) -> Tuple[bool, int]:\n    \"\"\"\n    Given a 2D numpy array and the indices of a cell, this function checks if the cell is part of a colored rectangular\n    block and returns the value of the most common color in that block.\n\n    Args:\n    - input_grid (np.ndarray): 2D numpy array representing the input grid\n    - i (int): row index of the cell\n    - j (int): column index of the cell\n\n    Returns:\n    - Tuple[bool, int]: A tuple containing a boolean flag and an integer value. The flag is True if the cell is part of a\n    colored rectangular block, False otherwise. The value is the most common color in the block, or 0 if the flag is False.\n    \"\"\"\n    color_counts = {}\n    color = input_grid[i][j]\n    if color == 0:\n        return (False, 0)\n    for row in range(i, len(input_grid)):\n        if input_grid[row][j] != color:\n            break\n        for col in range(j, len(input_grid[0])):\n            if input_grid[row][col] != color:\n                break\n            if input_grid[row][col] == color:\n                if color in color_counts:\n                    color_counts[color] += 1\n                else:\n                    color_counts[color] = 1\n    if len(color_counts) == 0:\n        return (False, 0)\n    most_common_color = max(color_counts, key=color_counts.get)\n    return (True, most_common_color)\ndef main(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    output_grid = [[0] * len(input_grid[0]) for _ in range(len(input_grid))]\n    for i in range(len(input_grid)):\n        for j in range(len(input_grid[0])):\n            if input_grid[i][j] == 0:\n                continue\n            else:\n                flag, value = get_most_common_color_in_block(input_grid)\n                if flag:\n                    output_grid[i][j] = value\n    return output_grid", "user_code": "def main(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    out